Package gov.nasa.gsfc.spdf.ssc

Class PeriodicRefreshedCache<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.gsfc.spdf.ssc.PeriodicRefreshedCache<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the information in the cache.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable
    public class PeriodicRefreshedCache<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.AutoCloseable
    This class implements a cache of information which is refreshed periodically. While this class' internal references to the cached information are updated in a thread safe mannor, this class provides no guarentee about concurrent access to the information itself. That is, refer to the documentation for a type T object for information about concurrent access to the cached object.
    Author:
    B. Harris

    • Constructor Detail

      • PeriodicRefreshedCache

        public PeriodicRefreshedCache​(java.util.concurrent.ScheduledExecutorService execService,
                              java.util.concurrent.Callable<T> refresher,
                              java.lang.String name,
                              long period,
                              java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit timeUnit,
                              long initialPeriod,
                              java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit initialTimeUnit)
        Creates a PeriodicRefreshedCache. The purpose of a separate initialPeriod value is so initial attempts to get the cached information happen more frequently than subsequent updates. Once an initial update is successful, subsequent updates will occur at the normal period.
        Parameters:
        execService - the ExecutorService to use when refreshing cached information.
        refresher - a Callable that produces a fresh copy of cached information.
        name - name of the cache to use in logging. This value is included in logging records. Since this class is generic with respect to what it caches, a name may be helpful when multiple instances are created for different information.
        period - period between successive updates.
        timeUnit - time unit of period value.
        initialPeriod - period between successive attempts to get the initial cache information.
        initialTimeUnit - time unit of initialPeriod value.

      • cancel

        public boolean cancel()
        Attempts to cancel the periodic cache refresh operation. In an environment such as a web application server (with a MananagedScheduledExecutorService), it is important to call this method to avoid leaving unnecessary refresh operations executing.
        Returns:
        false if the refresh operation could not be cancelled. Otherwise, true.

      • get

        public T get()
        Gets the cached information. The reference returned changes as the cache is refreshed so it is necessary to repeatedly call this method to get the lastest information.
        Returns:
        cached information or null. It is likely to be null initially before the first successful update has completed.
